The paper focuses on a software framework for cloud robotic applications, which involves both robotics and cloud computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the challenges of exploiting cloud resources in robotic software, which relates to distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The framework proposed in the paper also involves cooperation between the robot and the cloud to maintain specific QoS properties, which relates to distributed systems (cs.Distributed) and systems and control (cs.SY).
